"title": "5819: cowardice",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5819",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An unwillingness to act in a situation of danger or opposition, because of fear. Avoiding the source of one's anxiety or fear, rather than dealing with it directly.</p>\n<h2>Cowardice prevents people from acknowledging Jesus Christ publicly</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:42-John12:43\">JHN 12:42–12:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:13\">JHN 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:22-John9:23\">JHN 9:22–9:23</a> <em>parents of the man born blind</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:38\">JHN 19:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:19\">JHN 20:19</a></p>\n<h3>Cowardice inhibits bad as well as good behaviour</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:5\">MAT 14:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:26\">MAT 21:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:46\">MAT 21:46</a></p>\n<h3>Cowardice leads to avoidance of the difficulty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:56\">MAT 26:56</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:6-1Sam13:7\">1SA 13:6–13:7</a> <em>the Philistine threat</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:24\">1SA 17:24</a> <em>Goliath</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:2-1Kgs19:3\">1KI 19:2–19:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:10\">JON 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:69-Matt26:74\">MAT 26:69–26:74</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:66-Mark14:71\">MRK 14:66–14:71</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:57-Luke22:60\">LUK 22:57–22:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:15-John18:18\">JHN 18:15–18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:25-John18:27\">JHN 18:25–18:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:37\">LUK 8:37</a> <em>after the destruction of the pigs</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:12\">GAL 2:12</a> <em>Peter</em></p>\n<h3>Cowardice can spread within a group</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:8\">DEU 20:8</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:30-Num13:33\">NUM 13:30–13:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:8\">JOS 14:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:2-Judg7:3\">JDG 7:2–7:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:4\">JER 38:4</a></p>\n<h2>God can work through cowardice</h2>\n<h3>In humbling disobedient people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:36-Lev26:39\">LEV 26:36–26:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:15-Isa30:17\">ISA 30:15–30:17</a></p>\n<h3>In routing the enemy</h3>\n<p>Rahab and the Israelite spies:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:8-Josh2:11\">JOS 2:8–2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:24\">JOS 2:24</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:15-1Sam14:16\">1SA 14:15–14:16</a> <em>the Philistines</em></p>\n<h2>God gives hope to the cowardly or fearful</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:25\">PRO 29:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:27-Deut1:31\">DEU 1:27–1:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:10-Judg7:11\">JDG 7:10–7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:3-Ps56:4\">PSA 56:3–56:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:12-Isa51:15\">ISA 51:12–51:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:12-Luke21:19\">LUK 21:12–21:19</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:5-Luke4:10\">4:5–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:13\">ACT 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:29-Acts4:31\">ACT 4:29–4:31</a></p>\n<h2>Judgment on cowards</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></strong> <em>Where cowardice meant rejecting the gospel and denying Jesus Christ.</em></p>",
